In addition, adjustment for multiple testing was made by means of both Bonferroni correction and Benjamini-Hochberg procedure, which is considered more appropriate in an 'omics' setting than Bonferroni correction. Finally, 'sex*ceramides' interaction terms used to test the hypotheses that the effect of ceramides on MVO 2 was significantly different between men and women. All analyses were performed using the SAS statistical package, version 9.3 (SAS institute Inc., Cary, NC, USA) and R 3.1.2.
